<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Interpretations">Interpreta=
tions</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-brac=
ket">[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DIntegr=
al&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D8" title=3D"Edit section: Interpretation=
s"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></div>
<figure class=3D"mw-default-size" typeof=3D"mw:File/Thumb"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Integral_approximations_J.svg" class=3D"mw-fi=
le-description"><img src=3D"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/=
thumb/4/4a/Integral_approximations_J.svg/250px-Integral_approximations_J.sv=
g.png" decoding=3D"async" width=3D"250" height=3D"241" class=3D"mw-file-ele=
ment" data-file-width=3D"219" data-file-height=3D"211"></a><figcaption>Appr=
oximations to integral of <span class=3D"texhtml"><span class=3D"nowrap">=
=E2=88=9A<span style=3D"border-top:1px solid; padding:0 0.1em;"><i>x</i></s=
pan></span></span> from 0 to 1, with 5 yellow right endpoint partitions and=
 10 green left endpoint partitions</figcaption></figure>
<p>Integrals appear in many practical situations. For instance, from the le=
ngth, width and depth of a swimming pool which is rectangular with a flat b=
ottom, one can determine the volume of water it can contain, the area of it=
s surface, and the length of its edge. But if it is oval with a rounded bot=
tom, integrals are required to find exact and rigorous values for these qua=
ntities. In each case, one may divide the sought quantity into infinitely m=
any <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infinitesimal" title=3D"Infini=
tesimal">infinitesimal</a> pieces, then sum the pieces to achieve an accura=
te approximation.
</p><p>As another example, to find the area of the region bounded by the gr=
aph of the function <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>f</i>(<i>x</i>) =3D</span> <=
span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-=
math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><math xml=
ns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\textstyle {\sqrt {x}=
}}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
