          <msqrt>
            <mi>x</mi>
          </msqrt>
        </mrow>
      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\textstyle {\sqrt {x}}}</an=
notation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/02f01419d50f8331ed8f948d3b0dce7d5bd75950" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.838ex; width:3.266ex; height:2.843ex;" alt=3D"{\textstyle {\sqrt=
 {x}}}"></span> between <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i> =3D 0</span> and <=
span class=3D"texhtml"><i>x</i> =3D 1</span>, one can divide the interval i=
nto five pieces (<span class=3D"texhtml">0, 1/5, 2/5, ..., 1</span>), then =
construct rectangles using the right end height of each piece (thus <span c=
lass=3D"texhtml"><span class=3D"nowrap">=E2=88=9A<span style=3D"border-top:=
1px solid; padding:0 0.1em;">0</span></span>, <span class=3D"nowrap">=E2=88=
=9A<span style=3D"border-top:1px solid; padding:0 0.1em;">1/5</span></span>=
, <span class=3D"nowrap">=E2=88=9A<span style=3D"border-top:1px solid; padd=
ing:0 0.1em;">2/5</span></span>, ..., <span class=3D"nowrap">=E2=88=9A<span=
 style=3D"border-top:1px solid; padding:0 0.1em;">1</span></span></span>) a=
nd sum their areas to get the approximation
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e \textstyle {\sqrt {\frac {1}{5}}}\left({\frac {1}{5}}-0\right)+{\sqrt {\f=
rac {2}{5}}}\left({\frac {2}{5}}-{\frac {1}{5}}\right)+\cdots +{\sqrt {\fra=
c {5}{5}}}\left({\frac {5}{5}}-{\frac {4}{5}}\right)\approx 0.7497,}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mstyle displaystyle=3D"false" scriptlevel=3D"0">
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <msqrt>
              <mfrac>
                <mn>1</mn>
