<p>This partitions the interval <span class=3D"texhtml">[<i>a</i>, <i>b</i>=
]</span> into <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">n</=
span> sub-intervals <span class=3D"texhtml">[<i>x</i><sub><i>i</i>=E2=88=92=
1</sub>, <i>x</i><sub><i>i</i></sub>]</span> indexed by <span class=3D"texh=
tml mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">i</span>, each of which is "tagged" =
with a specific point <span class=3D"texhtml"><i>t</i><sub><i>i</i></sub> =
=E2=88=88 [<i>x</i><sub><i>i</i>=E2=88=921</sub>, <i>x</i><sub><i>i</i></su=
b>]</span>. A <i>Riemann sum</i> of a function <span class=3D"texhtml mvar"=
 style=3D"font-style:italic;">f</span> with respect to such a tagged partit=
ion is defined as
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e \sum _{i=3D1}^{n}f(t_{i})\,\Delta _{i};}">
