um _{i=3D1}^{n}f(t_{i})\,\Delta _{i};}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>thus each term of the sum is the area of a rectangle with height equal t=
o the function value at the chosen point of the given sub-interval, and wid=
th the same as the width of sub-interval, <span class=3D"texhtml">=CE=94<su=
b><i>i</i></sub> =3D <i>x</i><sub><i>i</i></sub>=E2=88=92<i>x</i><sub><i>i<=
/i>=E2=88=921</sub></span>. The <i>mesh</i> of such a tagged partition is t=
he width of the largest sub-interval formed by the partition, <span class=
=3D"texhtml">max<sub><i>i</i>=3D1...<i>n</i></sub> =CE=94<sub><i>i</i></sub=
></span>. The <i>Riemann integral</i> of a function <span class=3D"texhtml =
mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">f</span> over the interval <span class=
=3D"texhtml">[<i>a</i>, <i>b</i>]</span> is equal to <span class=3D"texhtml=
 mvar" style=3D"font-style:italic;">S</span> if:<sup id=3D"cite_ref-23" cla=
ss=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integral#cite_not=
e-23"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>22<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]=
</span></a></sup>
</p>
