<p>is a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_functional" class=
=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Linear functional">linear functional</a> on this =
vector space. Thus, the collection of integrable functions is closed under =
taking <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linear_combination" title=
=3D"Linear combination">linear combinations</a>, and the integral of a line=
ar combination is the linear combination of the integrals:<sup id=3D"cite_r=
ef-:0_31-0" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/In=
tegral#cite_note-:0-31"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>30<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
