,dx.}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>That is, the improper integral is the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Limit_(mathematics)" title=3D"Limit (mathematics)">limit</a> of prop=
er integrals as one endpoint of the interval of integration approaches eith=
er a specified <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Real_number" title=
=3D"Real number">real number</a>, or <span class=3D"texhtml">=E2=88=9E</spa=
n>, or <span class=3D"texhtml">=E2=88=92=E2=88=9E</span>. In more complicat=
ed cases, limits are required at both endpoints, or at interior points.
</p>
