      </mstyle>
    </mrow>
    <annotation encoding=3D"application/x-tex">{\displaystyle W=3D\mathbf {=
F} \cdot \mathbf {s} .}</annotation>
  </semantics>
</math></span><img src=3D"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/rend=
er/svg/2102143a354b5c4cfe19a50340a1b568219a49ea" class=3D"mwe-math-fallback=
-image-inline mw-invert skin-invert" aria-hidden=3D"true" style=3D"vertical=
-align: -0.338ex; width:10.598ex; height:2.176ex;" alt=3D"{\displaystyle W=
=3D\mathbf {F} \cdot \mathbf {s} .}"></span></dd></dl>
<p>For an object moving along a path <span class=3D"texhtml mvar" style=3D"=
font-style:italic;"><i>C</i></span> in a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Vector_field" title=3D"Vector field">vector field</a> <span class=3D=
"texhtml"><b>F</b></span> such as an <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wi=
ki/Electric_field" title=3D"Electric field">electric field</a> or <a href=
=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gravitational_field" title=3D"Gravitation=
al field">gravitational field</a>, the total work done by the field on the =
object is obtained by summing up the differential work done in moving from =
<span class=3D"texhtml"><b>s</b></span> to <span class=3D"texhtml"><b>s</b>=
 + <i>d</i><b>s</b></span>. This gives the line integral<sup id=3D"cite_ref=
-46" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Integral#=
cite_note-46"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>45<span class=3D"cite-br=
acket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
<dl><dd><span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span clas=
s=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;">=
<math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" alttext=3D"{\displaystyl=
e W=3D\int _{C}\mathbf {F} \cdot d\mathbf {s} .}">
  <semantics>
    <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
      <mstyle displaystyle=3D"true" scriptlevel=3D"0">
        <mi>W</mi>
        <mo>=3D</mo>
        <msub>
          <mo>=E2=88=AB<!-- =E2=88=AB --></mo>
          <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
            <mi>C</mi>
          </mrow>
        </msub>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
          <mi mathvariant=3D"bold">F</mi>
        </mrow>
        <mo>=E2=8B=85<!-- =E2=8B=85 --></mo>
        <mi>d</mi>
        <mrow class=3D"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD">
